<v Speaker 1>Now, another useful skill that we want in language learning is to work backwards, not just to work from the two form

00:01:09.660 --> 00:01:24.460
<v Speaker 1>take off the R or the R or the E and add bits on, but we want to get in the habit of also working backwards because maybe we see or hear somewhere a word like bamos and we want to be able to work backwards from bamos to get the other versions.

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:29.120
<v Speaker 1>Taking off the ending which is for we and putting our other bits on.

