<v Speaker 1>IR all by itself.

00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:56.640
<v Speaker 1>IR.

00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:58.319
<v Speaker 1>This is to go.

00:02:58.440 --> 00:03:09.239
<v Speaker 1>So it's it's very irregular and this is actually because this verb is two verbs that kind of stuck together to form one verb over time.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:19.160
<v Speaker 1>So in French you have like a aller, no, which means going, and in English we get alleyway from this, and alleyway is like a road, no?

00:03:19.160 --> 00:03:20.760
<v Speaker 1>And this is related to ir

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:30.000
<v Speaker 1>So ir comes from one verb historically and then the versions of ir actually come from a different verb

00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:34.500
<v Speaker 1>So they kind of stuck together over time and they give us this very irregular situation.

